WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

2
00:00:12.554 --> 00:00:15.682
{\an8}<i>Urine tests were conducted</i>
<i>in schools nationwide</i>

3
00:00:15.765 --> 00:00:17.600
{\an8}<i>under the ERPB's direction.</i>

4
00:00:17.684 --> 00:00:21.479
<i>The ERPB stated the tests were intended</i>
<i>to detect and treat at an early stage</i>

5
00:00:21.563 --> 00:00:25.275
<i>kidney abnormalities and diabetes-related</i>
<i>conditions among students.</i>

6
00:00:25.358 --> 00:00:27.110
<i>While some are questioning</i>

7
00:00:27.193 --> 00:00:31.031
<i>whether the tests are meant</i>
<i>to detect drug activity in schools.</i>

8
00:00:31.114 --> 00:00:34.993
<i>several schools have refused to take part.</i>
<i>citing final examinations.</i>

9
00:00:35.994 --> 00:00:38.329
<i>This is Seungyeon High School.</i>

10
00:00:38.413 --> 00:00:41.958
known as the most academically competitive
school in Gangnam.

11
00:00:42.042 --> 00:00:45.336
It also sends the most students
to SNU Medical School nationwide.

12
00:00:45.420 --> 00:00:47.505
You must know it well from living there.

13
00:00:48.089 --> 00:00:50.091
My mom wanted me to go to this school.

14
00:00:50.175 --> 00:00:52.927
so my family moved nearby
when I was seven.

15
00:00:53.011 --> 00:00:54.512
Weren't you at a science school?

16
00:00:57.307 --> 00:01:03.146
Seungyeon High School is known
for having very pushy parents.

17
00:01:03.646 --> 00:01:06.900
CLASS S

18
00:01:09.903 --> 00:01:12.405
This is the last exam
that counts for early admission.

19
00:01:12.906 --> 00:01:15.325
If you blow this.
the CSAT is your only option.

20
00:01:15.408 --> 00:01:17.869
Unless you want that. do well today.

21
00:01:17.952 --> 00:01:19.037
Yes. sir.

22
00:01:19.120 --> 00:01:20.663
Okay. let's get started.

23
00:01:42.102 --> 00:01:44.521
Is it Class 1. Class 2. and then Class S?

24
00:01:45.105 --> 00:01:48.817
I told you this school sends
the most students to med school in Seoul.

25
00:01:48.900 --> 00:01:52.987
This is a special class
for those aiming for med school.

26
00:01:53.613 --> 00:01:57.575
It's basically a class
of the school's top students.

27
00:02:33.903 --> 00:02:35.530
My boy!

28
00:02:37.282 --> 00:02:39.784
Congratulations
on getting into SNU Medical School!

29
00:02:39.868 --> 00:02:41.494
-My son!
-Congratulations!

30
00:02:41.578 --> 00:02:42.704
This is huge!

31
00:02:43.288 --> 00:02:44.247
Congrats!

32
00:02:49.836 --> 00:02:50.837
Congrats!

33
00:02:54.549 --> 00:02:56.092
Hyeon-min. congrats!

34
00:03:12.108 --> 00:03:13.067
Who are you?

35
00:03:13.151 --> 00:03:15.486
-We're from the ERPB.
-Hey. are you okay?

36
00:03:30.835 --> 00:03:32.170
His nose is bleeding.

37
00:03:32.253 --> 00:03:34.422
-Let's take him to the nurse's office.
-Okay.

38
00:03:35.340 --> 00:03:36.591
-Here.
-Let's get you up.

39
00:03:36.674 --> 00:03:38.426
Sir. where is the nurse's office?

40
00:03:38.509 --> 00:03:40.720
-Turn left. then go down.
-Left? Okay. thank you.

41
00:03:54.817 --> 00:03:55.818
-Here.
-Be careful.

42
00:03:55.902 --> 00:03:57.570
-Hold his head from the back.
-Okay.

43
00:04:08.373 --> 00:04:09.207
URINE TEST CHECKLIST

44
00:04:09.290 --> 00:04:10.208
Class 6…

45
00:04:10.291 --> 00:04:12.418
Stop the exam right now!

46
00:04:13.002 --> 00:04:14.963
My kid can't finish the exam!

47
00:04:18.508 --> 00:04:20.927
Do you want to see
my son and me die here today?

48
00:04:21.511 --> 00:04:23.888
Will you take responsibility
if he doesn't get in?

49
00:04:23.972 --> 00:04:26.182
Hyeon-min will take the exam
no matter what!

50
00:04:29.852 --> 00:04:31.479
-Jung Hyeon-min!
-Ma'am.

51
00:04:31.562 --> 00:04:33.523
He passed out in the middle of the exam.

52
00:04:34.941 --> 00:04:36.484
How much did you get done?

53
00:04:39.737 --> 00:04:41.572
It's okay. There's still time.

54
00:04:41.656 --> 00:04:44.409
I already talked to the teacher.
so just finish the exam.

55
00:04:44.492 --> 00:04:45.952
Can you get up?

56
00:04:48.621 --> 00:04:51.541
Mom. I don't feel so good.

57
00:04:51.624 --> 00:04:54.377
It's from staying up all night studying.
Everyone's the same.

58
00:04:55.169 --> 00:04:56.004
Here.

59
00:04:57.338 --> 00:04:58.715
But Mom.

60
00:04:59.424 --> 00:05:01.092
I keep having weird thoughts.

61
00:05:02.343 --> 00:05:04.929
Weird thoughts while studying
mean you're losing focus.

62
00:05:06.973 --> 00:05:08.808
I've brought your medicine.

63
00:05:08.891 --> 00:05:10.184
You'll feel better soon.

64
00:05:12.186 --> 00:05:13.438
Here.

65
00:05:18.109 --> 00:05:18.943
Here.

66
00:05:24.991 --> 00:05:26.576
You're almost there.

67
00:05:28.202 --> 00:05:31.331
You don't want all our hard work
to go to waste. do you?

68
00:05:31.998 --> 00:05:34.292
Hang in there. son. For me?

69
00:05:35.209 --> 00:05:36.961
All right. let's go.

70
00:05:58.566 --> 00:06:02.653
TEACH YOU A LESSON

71
00:06:08.451 --> 00:06:10.495
<i>Attention. students.</i>

72
00:06:10.578 --> 00:06:14.665
<i>There will now be an announcement</i>
<i>of special directives from the ERPB.</i>

73
00:06:14.749 --> 00:06:17.168
<i>All students are to remain on campus</i>

74
00:06:17.251 --> 00:06:20.797
<i>and prepare immediately for urine testing.</i>

75
00:06:25.718 --> 00:06:26.886
SON

76
00:06:30.848 --> 00:06:33.267
Hyeon-min. how did the exam go?

77
00:06:34.102 --> 00:06:35.395
Did you finish?

78
00:06:37.855 --> 00:06:38.898
Why?

79
00:06:39.982 --> 00:06:41.442
What? The ERPB?

80
00:06:42.193 --> 00:06:43.569
They must be crazy.

81
00:06:44.070 --> 00:06:44.904
Okay.

82
00:06:44.987 --> 00:06:47.490
I'll head over to school now.
Call the other moms.

83
00:06:47.573 --> 00:06:48.991
What? The ERPB?

84
00:06:50.034 --> 00:06:52.703
Are they crazy?
The kids have to go to <i>hagwon </i>now.

85
00:06:55.832 --> 00:06:57.375
Where do you think you're going?

86
00:06:57.959 --> 00:06:59.627
Didn't you hear about the test?

87
00:06:59.710 --> 00:07:01.087
We're going to <i>hagwon</i>.

88
00:07:01.170 --> 00:07:02.338
Go after the urine test.

89
00:07:02.422 --> 00:07:04.424
Our moms are coming. You can talk to them.

90
00:07:04.507 --> 00:07:06.884
-What are they doing?
-What's the point of this?

91
00:07:06.968 --> 00:07:09.887
Da-hui. what are you doing?
You'll be late for <i>hagwon</i>. Get going.

92
00:07:09.971 --> 00:07:12.140
-You go ahead.
-What are they doing?

93
00:07:12.223 --> 00:07:14.475
-Go quickly.
-What the hell are they doing?

94
00:07:20.565 --> 00:07:22.984
What do you think you're doing?

95
00:07:23.067 --> 00:07:26.404
-What do you think?
-Hyeon-min's mom. be quiet.

96
00:07:27.780 --> 00:07:30.992
Do you realize
how critical this period is for the kids?

97
00:07:31.826 --> 00:07:35.746
For top students. one point can move them
up or down several university tiers.

98
00:07:35.830 --> 00:07:39.750
There may be no guns. but students
and parents are fighting a war.

99
00:07:40.251 --> 00:07:42.587
So that's why you've put
lives on the line?

100
00:07:43.880 --> 00:07:47.216
You must've heard the rumors.
This test includes a drug screening.

101
00:07:47.967 --> 00:07:51.345
Drugs? Are you suggesting
our kids are on drugs?

102
00:07:53.848 --> 00:07:56.851
Those kids are applying
to SNU Medical School.

103
00:07:56.934 --> 00:07:59.854
-They're not like other kids.
-They all look the same to me.

104
00:08:01.814 --> 00:08:05.568
Have you even thought about what it took
for our kids to get this far?

105
00:08:06.694 --> 00:08:11.282
From birth through preschool.
elementary. middle. and high school.

106
00:08:11.365 --> 00:08:15.036
and now their most crucial year.
they have never wasted a single second.

107
00:08:15.119 --> 00:08:17.830
And what about the moms here?

108
00:08:18.331 --> 00:08:21.083
We sleep an hour less than our kids.
wake up an hour earlier.

109
00:08:21.167 --> 00:08:23.461
send them to <i>hagwon</i>. look for consultants…

110
00:08:24.712 --> 00:08:26.797
If you want them tested.
do it after the CSAT.

111
00:08:27.298 --> 00:08:30.676
Refusing the test will result
in a CSAT penalty. Is that okay?

112
00:08:30.760 --> 00:08:32.261
What do you mean "penalty"?

113
00:08:32.345 --> 00:08:34.514
Are you threatening us
with our kids' lives?

114
00:08:34.597 --> 00:08:36.098
If I were. would you listen?

115
00:08:36.182 --> 00:08:37.850
This is Daechi-dong!

116
00:08:37.934 --> 00:08:39.894
You think you can handle the moms here?

117
00:08:39.977 --> 00:08:40.811
Yes.

118
00:08:41.437 --> 00:08:42.688
The ERPB can handle them.

119
00:08:42.772 --> 00:08:43.814
Then go ahead.

120
00:08:43.898 --> 00:08:45.691
If you want to see people die.

121
00:08:45.775 --> 00:08:48.110
We're doing the test so no one dies.

122
00:08:48.194 --> 00:08:49.695
So we can save even one life

123
00:08:50.404 --> 00:08:51.989
before it's too late.

124
00:08:54.200 --> 00:08:56.160
There's an ERPB-designated hospital.

125
00:08:56.244 --> 00:08:59.288
Take your children there for testing
before school tomorrow.

126
00:08:59.372 --> 00:09:00.665
If you don't.

127
00:09:02.208 --> 00:09:04.293
you won't be able to handle
what comes next.

128
00:09:13.177 --> 00:09:15.346
You're Jung Hyeon-min's mother. right?

129
00:09:17.473 --> 00:09:19.892
Hyeon-min didn't look very well earlier.

130
00:09:19.976 --> 00:09:22.186
Make sure you take him
for the test tomorrow.

131
00:09:36.033 --> 00:09:37.159
By any chance.

132
00:09:38.119 --> 00:09:39.495
do you know who I am?

133
00:09:40.454 --> 00:09:42.957
Well. I've seen you on TV.

134
00:09:43.958 --> 00:09:46.377
You're someone very important.

135
00:09:49.171 --> 00:09:51.757
You hurt your hand
because of the EPRB. right?

136
00:09:51.841 --> 00:09:53.134
Oh. no.

137
00:09:53.217 --> 00:09:55.219
It was my fault.

138
00:09:55.303 --> 00:09:58.681
I'm not trying to blame the ERPB.

139
00:09:59.181 --> 00:10:01.183
I'm trying to help you.

140
00:10:02.435 --> 00:10:03.811
Me? Why?

141
00:10:04.812 --> 00:10:07.523
Providing opportunities
to those who need them

142
00:10:08.107 --> 00:10:09.817
is my job as a politician.

143
00:10:11.736 --> 00:10:13.487
Can I look at your hand again?

144
00:10:15.406 --> 00:10:17.408
It doesn't look like a minor injury.

145
00:10:17.491 --> 00:10:19.243
How about treatment on the outside?

146
00:10:22.371 --> 00:10:26.751
<i>Recently. an armed attack broke out</i>
<i>in a juvenile prison.</i>

147
00:10:26.834 --> 00:10:29.879
{\an8}<i>A juvenile offender</i>
<i>under the ERPB's supervision</i>

148
00:10:29.962 --> 00:10:32.548
{\an8}<i>was attacked with a weapon by an inmate.</i>

149
00:10:32.632 --> 00:10:35.217
<i>It could have caused</i>
<i>serious harm or loss of life. but…</i>

150
00:10:35.301 --> 00:10:36.594
-What?
-Oh. nothing.

151
00:10:36.677 --> 00:10:38.179
<i>…the juvenile was unharmed.</i>

152
00:10:39.430 --> 00:10:42.642
<i>However. the inmate who protected him</i>
<i>was the perpetrator of…</i>

153
00:10:42.725 --> 00:10:43.934
-Where is it?
-Well…

154
00:10:44.018 --> 00:10:45.102
That way. sir.

155
00:10:45.186 --> 00:10:46.771
-Lead the way. Hurry up.
-Yes. sir.

156
00:10:47.355 --> 00:10:48.939
<i>They deliberately chose where…</i>

157
00:10:49.023 --> 00:10:52.401
-I wonder where the toilet--
-You're making me more aware of it.

158
00:10:52.485 --> 00:10:54.695
I already saw it all earlier.

159
00:10:55.196 --> 00:10:57.323
Look at you trying so hard.

160
00:10:57.406 --> 00:10:59.659
-Are you okay?
-Of course not.

161
00:10:59.742 --> 00:11:00.993
-That damn photo.
-Come on.

162
00:11:01.077 --> 00:11:02.495
-How did they get it?
-Let's go.

163
00:11:02.578 --> 00:11:04.538
Are the Seungyeon High kids being tested?

164
00:11:04.622 --> 00:11:06.457
Yes. they are.

165
00:11:13.881 --> 00:11:14.757
Need some air?

166
00:11:15.341 --> 00:11:16.217
Let's go outside.

167
00:11:24.225 --> 00:11:25.226
Drink this.

168
00:11:28.270 --> 00:11:30.189
Are you okay? Feeling better?

169
00:11:30.272 --> 00:11:32.149
I'm feeling a bit better.

170
00:11:32.233 --> 00:11:33.192
Good.

171
00:11:37.697 --> 00:11:40.032
REPORT CARDS WERE DISTRIBUTED
TO STUDENTS TODAY

172
00:11:41.033 --> 00:11:42.326
Report cards are out.

173
00:11:42.410 --> 00:11:44.745
-They've also been sent by email. Check.
-Right.

174
00:11:57.174 --> 00:12:00.428
I passed out during the exam
for that subject.

175
00:12:03.472 --> 00:12:04.682
I'm sorry. Mom.

176
00:12:12.064 --> 00:12:13.816
What did I tell you?

177
00:12:15.901 --> 00:12:19.780
Kids like you who can't handle pressure
should at least take your meds properly.

178
00:12:21.407 --> 00:12:23.492
Is it really that hard to take your meds?

179
00:12:25.327 --> 00:12:27.496
Don't you feel sorry for me?

180
00:12:28.205 --> 00:12:31.417
I've had to swallow my pride
in front of the other moms because of you.

181
00:12:33.294 --> 00:12:35.421
Did I ever ask for recognition?

182
00:12:37.131 --> 00:12:39.133
All I'm asking is for you to study.

183
00:12:42.052 --> 00:12:44.138
If you knew how hard I've worked…

184
00:12:47.183 --> 00:12:49.518
For God's sake…

185
00:13:20.674 --> 00:13:24.428
<i>Hyeon-min's goal is SNU Medical School.</i>

186
00:13:24.512 --> 00:13:28.933
I've heard you're a well-known consultant
for medical school admissions.

187
00:13:29.642 --> 00:13:33.270
I'll start by assessing his level.
How advanced is he in his studies?

188
00:13:34.396 --> 00:13:36.398
I've had him study ahead.

189
00:13:36.482 --> 00:13:39.819
He's in first year middle school
but is doing first-year high school math.

190
00:13:39.902 --> 00:13:42.696
He still hasn't finished high school math?

191
00:13:44.281 --> 00:13:46.075
He'll catch up soon.

192
00:13:46.575 --> 00:13:48.953
Our Hyeon-min is top in his grade.

193
00:13:49.036 --> 00:13:52.915
A top student in a provincial school
becomes bottom-tier in Gangnam.

194
00:13:53.499 --> 00:13:55.543
Don't even think about med school.

195
00:13:57.127 --> 00:13:59.547
This isn't exactly the provinces.

196
00:13:59.630 --> 00:14:00.756
We're next to Seoul.

197
00:14:00.840 --> 00:14:02.800
You should meet my son first.
Once you do--

198
00:14:02.883 --> 00:14:04.760
Do you know when moms in Gangnam

199
00:14:04.844 --> 00:14:07.054
start preparing their kids
for SNU's med school?

200
00:14:09.014 --> 00:14:10.266
The moment they're born.

201
00:14:11.058 --> 00:14:13.686
They map out a 20-year plan.
from birth to med school.

202
00:14:13.769 --> 00:14:18.023
and choose preschools. schools. <i>hagwons</i>.
and private tutors accordingly.

203
00:14:18.107 --> 00:14:20.985
These kids have been preparing
for over a decade longer

204
00:14:21.068 --> 00:14:22.945
than those who start in middle school.

205
00:14:24.280 --> 00:14:25.865
By Hyeon-min's age.

206
00:14:25.948 --> 00:14:29.326
he should've already finished studying
the core concepts of the CSAT.

207
00:14:29.410 --> 00:14:32.371
He should be practicing questions
to avoid mistakes on the exam

208
00:14:32.454 --> 00:14:35.749
and working on med school interviews.
essay writing. and English.

209
00:14:36.959 --> 00:14:40.963
Do you understand
just how far behind Hyeon-min is?

210
00:14:41.797 --> 00:14:43.924
Still. he's really…

211
00:14:45.593 --> 00:14:46.635
Kids in Daechi-dong

212
00:14:47.928 --> 00:14:50.514
are tackling questions at this level
right now.

213
00:14:53.559 --> 00:14:54.727
How many of them

214
00:14:55.811 --> 00:14:58.147
do you think Hyeon-min could answer?

215
00:15:16.040 --> 00:15:18.083
DAECHI SKY REAL ESTATE

216
00:15:20.044 --> 00:15:23.339
PRIME LISTING
A HOME THAT SENT KIDS TO SNU MED SCHOOL

217
00:15:23.422 --> 00:15:25.215
GRAND PRIZE IN ENGLISH. JUNG HYEON-MIN

218
00:15:26.467 --> 00:15:29.053
Do you really have to live
in a place like this?

219
00:15:30.095 --> 00:15:32.890
It's within walking distance
of the school and <i>hagwon.</i>

220
00:15:32.973 --> 00:15:34.558
and a bargain for Gangnam.

221
00:15:34.642 --> 00:15:38.354
Besides. the two sons
who grew up here got into SNU.

222
00:15:38.854 --> 00:15:40.314
I even got it with no markup.

223
00:15:40.397 --> 00:15:42.524
I'm not sure about this.

224
00:15:42.608 --> 00:15:45.611
A school is a school.
This area can't be that special.

225
00:15:45.694 --> 00:15:47.237
You have no idea.

226
00:15:47.321 --> 00:15:50.616
Seungyeon High has a med school prep class
just for the top ten students.

227
00:15:50.699 --> 00:15:54.286
If you get into this class.
you're guaranteed SNU med school.

228
00:15:54.370 --> 00:15:56.747
Hyeon-min's goal
is to get into this class.

229
00:15:57.957 --> 00:16:00.793
But still. this place is just…

230
00:16:01.502 --> 00:16:03.212
Aren't you upset?

231
00:16:03.712 --> 00:16:05.631
Didn't your brother go to med school?

232
00:16:05.714 --> 00:16:08.425
Does your family treat you two the same?

233
00:16:08.509 --> 00:16:14.306
But thanks to him. I work at his clinic.
so don't be like that.

234
00:16:14.390 --> 00:16:17.184
That's exactly why
you and I get treated like that

235
00:16:17.267 --> 00:16:19.561
and why Hyeon-min does too.

236
00:16:19.645 --> 00:16:22.189
I'll make sure
Hyeon-min gets into med school

237
00:16:22.272 --> 00:16:23.315
so he's respected.

238
00:16:23.399 --> 00:16:25.567
Who says he's not respected?

239
00:16:25.651 --> 00:16:27.236
That's enough!

240
00:16:28.445 --> 00:16:31.240
Don't be so discouraging.
Just take the door off.

241
00:16:31.782 --> 00:16:33.158
Fine. I will.

242
00:16:36.245 --> 00:16:37.621
I got it.

243
00:16:38.122 --> 00:16:39.581
Okay. hold it.

244
00:16:46.630 --> 00:16:49.383
GOAL
GET INTO SEUNGYEON HIGH!

245
00:16:53.012 --> 00:16:56.682
GOAL
GET INTO SNU MEDICAL SCHOOL!

246
00:17:11.655 --> 00:17:12.489
Here.

247
00:17:13.866 --> 00:17:18.245
I'm not the only one making a fuss.
All the moms around here are like this.

248
00:17:19.329 --> 00:17:20.164
Okay.

249
00:17:21.248 --> 00:17:22.708
Oh. Mom.

250
00:17:23.208 --> 00:17:28.047
What about tutoring?
All the kids seem to have the same tutor.

251
00:17:28.839 --> 00:17:31.091
I'm looking into it. so don't worry.

252
00:17:31.633 --> 00:17:32.551
Keep studying.

253
00:17:38.807 --> 00:17:42.811
<i>Yeong-jun's mom. do you think</i>
<i>you can invite me to the moms' meetings?</i>

254
00:17:50.736 --> 00:17:51.570
Here.

255
00:17:52.321 --> 00:17:53.322
Enjoy.

256
00:17:54.698 --> 00:17:56.450
Forget about all the other moms.

257
00:17:56.533 --> 00:17:58.827
Just stay on Da-hui's mom's good side.

258
00:17:59.328 --> 00:18:00.621
She's the mama pig.

259
00:18:00.704 --> 00:18:01.872
The mama pig?

260
00:18:01.955 --> 00:18:04.666
You know how a sow
has all her piglets following her?

261
00:18:04.750 --> 00:18:07.961
She has all the moms trailing after her.
so she's called the mama pig.

262
00:18:11.673 --> 00:18:14.510
But it's not something just anyone can do.

263
00:18:14.593 --> 00:18:16.970
Information is power for moms here.

264
00:18:17.596 --> 00:18:20.766
And Da-hui's mom has all the connections
with academic coordinators.

265
00:18:20.849 --> 00:18:22.726
admissions consultants.

266
00:18:22.810 --> 00:18:27.189
and even <i>hagwons</i>
with special programs for SNU med school.

267
00:18:27.272 --> 00:18:29.691
You're not a working mom. are you?

268
00:18:29.775 --> 00:18:32.319
No. I'm not. Why?

269
00:18:32.402 --> 00:18:35.322
Working moms. or parents who both work.
can't join this circle.

270
00:18:35.405 --> 00:18:40.202
They just take information and act busy
when it actually matters.

271
00:18:40.285 --> 00:18:44.373
But doctors and professors
get a free pass no matter what.

272
00:18:44.957 --> 00:18:46.208
How come?

273
00:18:46.291 --> 00:18:49.711
You need a strategic student profile
for early admissions.

274
00:18:49.795 --> 00:18:53.674
Hospital volunteer work
and university lab research

275
00:18:53.757 --> 00:18:56.301
make the ultimate student profile.

276
00:18:56.385 --> 00:18:59.138
With Da-hui's mom. it's a done deal.

277
00:19:00.973 --> 00:19:03.433
I'd better stay on her good side.

278
00:19:13.485 --> 00:19:15.279
It's not bedtime yet.

279
00:19:15.362 --> 00:19:16.530
I'm sorry.

280
00:19:17.030 --> 00:19:18.282
I was just so sleepy.

281
00:19:18.365 --> 00:19:20.576
You must be tired. Eat while you study.

282
00:19:22.077 --> 00:19:24.121
Can I have a little more?

283
00:19:24.204 --> 00:19:27.541
A full stomach makes you sleepy.
Your brain only needs glucose.

284
00:19:28.292 --> 00:19:31.712
Just eat this and focus a bit more.

285
00:19:31.795 --> 00:19:32.629
Okay?

286
00:19:40.721 --> 00:19:42.097
Hi. honey.

287
00:19:44.141 --> 00:19:47.352
We're already here.
and you live by yourself.

288
00:19:47.436 --> 00:19:51.231
You can move to a cheaper studio
or move in with your mother.

289
00:19:52.900 --> 00:19:55.068
It's all for Hyeon-min!

290
00:20:00.449 --> 00:20:02.159
Once he succeeds.

291
00:20:02.743 --> 00:20:04.161
it will all be worth it.

292
00:20:19.968 --> 00:20:21.762
I didn't want to come empty-handed.

293
00:20:22.262 --> 00:20:23.972
I hope you like it.

294
00:20:25.724 --> 00:20:27.226
You didn't have to.

295
00:20:32.856 --> 00:20:35.108
I came to see you because--

296
00:20:35.192 --> 00:20:37.653
Every mom comes to see me
for the same reason.

297
00:20:37.736 --> 00:20:39.613
And I already heard from Yeong-jun's mom.

298
00:20:40.489 --> 00:20:43.992
Just come to a few of our meetings
and see how it goes.

299
00:20:46.245 --> 00:20:47.079
Okay.

300
00:20:47.579 --> 00:20:49.164
Was it? Was it okay?

301
00:20:50.123 --> 00:20:51.166
What would you like?

302
00:20:51.250 --> 00:20:53.460
-I'll have an iced latte.
-A latte.

303
00:20:53.543 --> 00:20:55.921
-Double shot. please.
-Double shot? Okay.

304
00:20:56.004 --> 00:20:57.547
DOUBLE SHOT

305
00:20:58.382 --> 00:21:01.176
-This is already too much.
-This is only the start. okay?

306
00:21:02.052 --> 00:21:02.970
Here you go.

307
00:21:03.053 --> 00:21:05.013
Here's your latte.

308
00:21:05.097 --> 00:21:07.849
-She's a natural.
-Yeah. you're right. It's Da-hui.

309
00:21:07.933 --> 00:21:09.518
That's why she's at that level.

310
00:21:09.601 --> 00:21:12.229
For math. Ms. Jung Da-eun is the best.

311
00:21:13.355 --> 00:21:15.148
She gets kids into SNU med school.

312
00:21:15.232 --> 00:21:16.483
MATH
JUNG DA-EUN

313
00:21:16.566 --> 00:21:18.819
One downside is
that her academic background isn't great.

314
00:21:25.742 --> 00:21:27.661
ENGLISH
OH BO-HYEON

315
00:21:31.206 --> 00:21:34.334
It's easier if you start
by calculating 6 choose 2.

316
00:21:34.835 --> 00:21:35.961
What's 6 choose 2?

317
00:21:36.044 --> 00:21:38.213
Then what's 15 times 6?

318
00:21:38.297 --> 00:21:39.965
-90.
-That's correct.

319
00:21:40.048 --> 00:21:43.427
90 is correct. Try solving this one
and see if you understand.

320
00:21:43.510 --> 00:21:45.220
REPORT CARD
YEAR 1. SEMESTER 1. 2024

321
00:22:03.572 --> 00:22:04.906
Don't worry.

322
00:22:04.990 --> 00:22:07.367
They say grades
depend on how much parents put in.

323
00:22:07.451 --> 00:22:08.285
Go on.

324
00:22:14.541 --> 00:22:17.252
For God's sake.

325
00:22:22.257 --> 00:22:24.259
It turns out these plates come as a set.

326
00:22:24.343 --> 00:22:27.346
If I'd known. I would've brought
the whole set last time.

327
00:22:28.638 --> 00:22:29.890
You didn't have to.

328
00:22:31.600 --> 00:22:33.018
I heard about Hyeon-min.

329
00:22:33.101 --> 00:22:35.812
He didn't get into
the med school prep class again. right?

330
00:22:35.896 --> 00:22:42.361
I got him the tutor you recommended.
and he goes to the same <i>hagwon </i>as Da-hui.

331
00:22:42.444 --> 00:22:44.613
so I don't know what the problem is.

332
00:22:44.696 --> 00:22:48.241
Sitting at a desk for hours
doesn't guarantee good grades.

333
00:22:48.325 --> 00:22:50.160
Even with the same study time.

334
00:22:50.243 --> 00:22:54.623
some kids take in 100%.
while others only take in 50%.

335
00:22:55.123 --> 00:22:56.958
That's the difference in focus.

336
00:22:58.085 --> 00:23:00.504
Is there a tutor for that too?

337
00:23:03.215 --> 00:23:06.635
There are things a teacher can help with
and things they can't.

338
00:23:09.763 --> 00:23:10.806
Hold on.

339
00:23:22.651 --> 00:23:25.070
Here. try giving him this.

340
00:23:25.570 --> 00:23:27.906
His focus will improve dramatically.

341
00:23:27.989 --> 00:23:31.618
Da-hui and her older brother took it.
and their grades went up.

342
00:23:55.725 --> 00:23:56.601
Hyeon-min.

343
00:23:59.354 --> 00:24:03.733
I went through a lot to get this for you
so you can study better.

344
00:24:04.359 --> 00:24:07.821
I know you'd do so well
if you really got your head in the game.

345
00:24:07.904 --> 00:24:09.322
I hear this stuff is amazing.

346
00:24:09.406 --> 00:24:12.409
You'll focus better
and be less nervous during exams.

347
00:24:13.326 --> 00:24:15.745
All the kids around here take it.

348
00:24:24.796 --> 00:24:25.630
Drink this.

349
00:24:29.718 --> 00:24:31.928
<i>This is an illegal drug.</i>

350
00:24:33.763 --> 00:24:35.891
You all look like you already knew.

351
00:24:36.933 --> 00:24:39.853
It's an unapproved ADHD medication
in Korea.

352
00:24:39.936 --> 00:24:43.607
Yet it has already been circulating
discreetly among mothers

353
00:24:43.690 --> 00:24:44.983
because it's effective.

354
00:24:45.484 --> 00:24:46.401
I'm sure you know.

355
00:24:48.820 --> 00:24:52.449
In the urine tests.
the children tested positive

356
00:24:52.532 --> 00:24:54.367
for methylphenidate and atomoxetine.

357
00:24:54.451 --> 00:24:58.455
These two drugs
are only for high-risk patients

358
00:24:58.538 --> 00:25:00.790
and are very rarely prescribed together.

359
00:25:00.874 --> 00:25:03.210
In particular.
methylphenidate is classified

360
00:25:03.293 --> 00:25:06.254
as a controlled psychotropic substance

361
00:25:06.338 --> 00:25:08.423
under the Narcotics Control Act in Korea.

362
00:25:09.007 --> 00:25:12.344
This means taking it
without a prescription is illegal.

363
00:25:14.179 --> 00:25:18.683
It violates the Narcotics Control Act
and the Pharmaceutical Affairs Act.

364
00:25:18.767 --> 00:25:20.602
making it a criminal offense.

365
00:25:21.228 --> 00:25:22.062
It'll be okay.

366
00:25:22.145 --> 00:25:23.939
Everyone here will be subject

367
00:25:24.606 --> 00:25:26.525
to police questioning.

368
00:25:29.569 --> 00:25:30.654
Inspector.

369
00:25:30.737 --> 00:25:31.571
Yes?

370
00:25:31.655 --> 00:25:34.574
The test results for Jung Hyeon-min
are concerning.

371
00:25:35.909 --> 00:25:37.244
Hyeon-min's mom.

372
00:25:38.411 --> 00:25:40.497
Where did Hyeon-min's mother go?

373
00:25:40.580 --> 00:25:44.167
-Hyeon-min's mom? Where did she go?
-I think she went out that way.

374
00:25:44.251 --> 00:25:45.293
Maybe to the bathroom?

375
00:25:45.377 --> 00:25:47.379
<i>I heard Hyeon-min's grades have gone up.</i>

376
00:25:49.089 --> 00:25:51.508
He must have been really determined.

377
00:25:51.591 --> 00:25:52.884
He's completely changed.

378
00:25:52.968 --> 00:25:55.053
He seems to have gotten mentally stronger.

379
00:25:55.136 --> 00:25:57.806
I think he'll make it
into the med school prep class soon.

380
00:25:58.473 --> 00:26:00.934
Still. the competition is really intense.

381
00:26:01.434 --> 00:26:06.147
Do you know of any medicine
that's better than the one you gave me?

382
00:26:06.231 --> 00:26:07.190
Well.

383
00:26:07.274 --> 00:26:11.027
I could find out if I looked into it.
but that one should be enough.

384
00:26:11.945 --> 00:26:12.862
I see.

385
00:26:15.407 --> 00:26:19.202
<i>My child's grades improved</i>
<i>after taking ADHD medication.</i>

386
00:26:19.286 --> 00:26:23.707
<i>I'm looking for something more effective.</i>
<i>If anyone knows. please help.</i>

387
00:26:24.374 --> 00:26:26.918
<i>Could you tell me what medication he took</i>
<i>that improved his grades?</i>

388
00:26:27.002 --> 00:26:29.170
They're no help at all.

389
00:26:33.883 --> 00:26:36.511
<i>I have the meds</i>
<i>last year's top med school entrant took.</i>

390
00:26:36.595 --> 00:26:37.762
<i>Do you want it?</i>

391
00:27:06.333 --> 00:27:08.043
You're from the forum. right?

392
00:27:08.877 --> 00:27:09.711
Yes.

393
00:27:35.070 --> 00:27:38.198
TIER 1

394
00:27:45.747 --> 00:27:48.083
Well done. my son.

395
00:27:49.209 --> 00:27:51.419
Can you get
into the med school prep class now?

396
00:27:51.503 --> 00:27:54.798
Yes. they told me
to join the class tomorrow.

397
00:27:57.092 --> 00:27:57.926
That's great.

398
00:28:00.929 --> 00:28:01.888
Well done.

399
00:28:12.190 --> 00:28:13.692
JUNG HYEON-MIN'S MOTHER

400
00:28:13.775 --> 00:28:15.777
She's still not picking up.

401
00:28:15.860 --> 00:28:18.947
They found another substance
in Hyeon-min's system besides ADHD meds.

402
00:28:19.030 --> 00:28:20.365
It's in the Heart Pills too.

403
00:28:20.448 --> 00:28:21.408
What?

404
00:28:23.410 --> 00:28:25.495
The amount is almost a lethal dose.

405
00:28:26.496 --> 00:28:29.082
If he keeps taking it
or increases the dose.

406
00:28:29.165 --> 00:28:30.709
couldn't it be life-threatening?

407
00:28:30.792 --> 00:28:33.128
-That's right.
-"That's right"? It's not…

408
00:28:33.628 --> 00:28:35.046
Are you crawling or what?

409
00:28:35.547 --> 00:28:36.631
I'm on it. kid!

410
00:28:44.931 --> 00:28:46.099
Hyeon-min.

411
00:28:46.933 --> 00:28:48.017
It's not your fault.

412
00:28:49.269 --> 00:28:50.603
You just got unlucky.

413
00:28:51.229 --> 00:28:53.565
Early admission is out.
but you still have the CSAT.

414
00:28:53.648 --> 00:28:56.025
If you do well.
you can still get into med school.

415
00:28:59.487 --> 00:29:01.823
You can pull yourself together
and do this. right?

416
00:29:03.283 --> 00:29:06.828
I'll get you excused for field study.
so don't go to school.

417
00:29:06.911 --> 00:29:09.247
Just study at home until the CSAT.

418
00:29:09.330 --> 00:29:10.331
Okay?

419
00:29:15.462 --> 00:29:16.546
Mom.

420
00:29:18.256 --> 00:29:19.883
Can you get me the meds?

421
00:29:21.342 --> 00:29:22.177
Yes.

422
00:29:22.677 --> 00:29:24.179
Let's take the meds and study.

423
00:29:43.448 --> 00:29:44.449
Hyeon-min.

424
00:29:45.867 --> 00:29:46.701
Jung Hyeon-min!

425
00:29:51.748 --> 00:29:53.208
Hyeon-min. are you in there?

426
00:29:55.835 --> 00:29:57.629
HIGH SCHOOL SENIOR INSIDE
DO NOT RING!

427
00:30:07.472 --> 00:30:08.723
Oh no.

428
00:30:15.730 --> 00:30:17.357
They won't let me in.

429
00:30:17.440 --> 00:30:18.983
All right. sir.

430
00:30:20.860 --> 00:30:22.946
-What did he say?
-They won't let him in.

431
00:30:24.823 --> 00:30:26.658
However I see it. it seems dangerous.

432
00:30:26.741 --> 00:30:28.868
You're not actually going to jump.
are you?

433
00:30:28.952 --> 00:30:31.204
-The kid might die at this rate.
-What?

434
00:30:35.667 --> 00:30:37.836
Oh my God. why are you up there?

435
00:30:38.503 --> 00:30:39.838
Hold that tight. okay?

436
00:30:41.381 --> 00:30:42.382
Oh my God!

437
00:30:44.634 --> 00:30:45.468
Wait.

438
00:31:07.156 --> 00:31:09.784
Wait. Hyeon-min! The ERPB is here.

439
00:31:22.088 --> 00:31:23.506
Inspector Im Han-rim!

440
00:31:23.590 --> 00:31:25.592
Are you all right?

441
00:31:26.634 --> 00:31:28.219
-What the…
-Hyeon-min!

442
00:31:28.303 --> 00:31:29.679
-Let go.
-No.

443
00:31:29.762 --> 00:31:32.181
-Give me the pills!
-No! Let go!

444
00:31:32.682 --> 00:31:34.225
No!

445
00:31:34.309 --> 00:31:36.227
-Take Hyeon-min to the hospital.
-Okay.

446
00:31:37.562 --> 00:31:39.522
No. you can't!

447
00:31:39.606 --> 00:31:41.482
-Let go. Hyeon-min!
-Come on!

448
00:31:42.191 --> 00:31:43.735
Let me go. Hyeon-min!

449
00:31:43.818 --> 00:31:45.612
Let me go. Hyeon-min!

450
00:31:48.615 --> 00:31:50.700
Why are you taking Hyeon-min?

451
00:31:52.702 --> 00:31:55.246
Ma'am. do you know
what kind of medication this is?

452
00:31:56.998 --> 00:31:59.334
Some students call it
a pill that keeps them awake.

453
00:31:59.417 --> 00:32:00.960
helps them focus.

454
00:32:01.044 --> 00:32:03.630
treats ADHD. boosts their grades.

455
00:32:03.713 --> 00:32:05.465
and gets them into med school.

456
00:32:05.548 --> 00:32:06.966
But we call it

457
00:32:07.467 --> 00:32:09.135
a pill that kills people.

458
00:32:10.803 --> 00:32:12.597
We call it an illicit drug.

459
00:32:15.558 --> 00:32:17.894
-What do you mean "illicit drug"?
-Didn't you know?

460
00:32:19.354 --> 00:32:20.563
No.

461
00:32:21.147 --> 00:32:24.067
I just gave it to him
because I heard it helps with focus.

462
00:32:24.150 --> 00:32:25.318
Did you really not know?

463
00:32:25.401 --> 00:32:27.111
How could I have?

464
00:32:27.195 --> 00:32:29.614
This is the first time
I'm hearing that it's bad!

465
00:32:29.697 --> 00:32:31.449
Did you really not know?

466
00:32:32.325 --> 00:32:34.452
Did you really not see
the changes in Hyeon-min…

467
00:32:36.871 --> 00:32:38.414
after he started taking it?

468
00:32:47.340 --> 00:32:48.216
Hyeon-min.

469
00:32:54.973 --> 00:32:56.641
Here. I got you. Oh my!

470
00:32:59.268 --> 00:33:00.895
I WANT TO DIE

471
00:33:00.979 --> 00:33:03.356
<i>You knew this drug</i>

472
00:33:03.898 --> 00:33:05.608
<i>was ruining Hyeon-min.</i>

473
00:33:25.086 --> 00:33:26.629
What were you thinking?

474
00:33:26.713 --> 00:33:28.548
As long as he could get into med school.

475
00:33:29.549 --> 00:33:32.260
you thought it was okay
to give him drugs like this?

476
00:33:33.720 --> 00:33:36.097
I was only going to give it to him
until the CSAT.

477
00:33:36.180 --> 00:33:38.975
Something could go wrong
with him before then.

478
00:33:39.058 --> 00:33:40.893
Is med school worth more than your son?

479
00:33:46.649 --> 00:33:48.443
I guess it is.

480
00:33:49.152 --> 00:33:50.820
He's almost there.

481
00:33:51.320 --> 00:33:54.365
Every second counts.
There's no time for this!

482
00:33:54.449 --> 00:33:56.617
Hyeon-min needs to study!

483
00:33:57.201 --> 00:33:58.286
From this moment on.

484
00:33:58.369 --> 00:34:01.080
you are not allowed
to leave this apartment.

485
00:34:01.164 --> 00:34:02.290
Why not?

486
00:34:02.373 --> 00:34:03.624
This is my home!

487
00:34:03.708 --> 00:34:05.376
This is to protect Hyeon-min.

488
00:34:05.460 --> 00:34:09.255
The ERPB will now separate
the child abuser from the victim.

489
00:34:09.338 --> 00:34:11.340
What do you mean "child abuse"?

490
00:34:11.424 --> 00:34:13.593
I'm his mother!

491
00:34:13.676 --> 00:34:16.804
I told you this is the most important time
of his life!

492
00:34:17.722 --> 00:34:21.517
Will you take responsibility
if he misses out on med school?

493
00:34:28.191 --> 00:34:30.276
If you want med school that badly.

494
00:34:32.153 --> 00:34:33.446
go yourself.

495
00:34:46.793 --> 00:34:48.294
Hyeon-min. are you okay?

496
00:34:50.671 --> 00:34:52.006
Oh my God. no!

497
00:34:54.634 --> 00:34:56.135
What are you doing?

498
00:34:57.595 --> 00:34:58.429
It's okay.

499
